<paragraph blockId="132.[151,1436,151,2006]" pageId="132" pageNumber="133">
Note on 
<typeStatus box="[298,346,152,176]" pageId="132" pageNumber="133">type</typeStatus>
material: W.R. Sherriffs collected 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1878" box="[742,844,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Psechridae" genus="Psechrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="132" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[742,844,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="133">Psechrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the highlands of central 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1239,151,175]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="132" pageNumber="133">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sherriffs, W. R." box="[1256,1424,151,175]" pageId="132" pageNumber="133" pagination="220 - 253" refId="ref125855" refString="Sherriffs, W. R. (1919) A contribution to the study of South Indian Arachnology. Annuals and Magazine of Natural History, (9 th Series) 4, 220 - 253." type="journal article" year="1919">Sherriffs 1919</bibRefCitation>
). He observed the webs of what he thought to be 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[683,780,188,211]" class="Arachnida" family="Psechridae" genus="Psechrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="132" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torvus">
<emphasis box="[683,780,188,211]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="133">P. torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the area of Nawalapitiya (
<bibRefCitation author="Sherriffs, W. R." box="[1104,1270,187,211]" pageId="132" pageNumber="133" pagination="220 - 253" refId="ref125855" refString="Sherriffs, W. R. (1919) A contribution to the study of South Indian Arachnology. Annuals and Magazine of Natural History, (9 th Series) 4, 220 - 253." type="journal article" year="1919">Sherriffs 1919</bibRefCitation>
). It is not clear if he had collected more material than what is deposited in ZMUC. It is also not clear if all the specimens were collected in the area of Nawalapitiya, but at least he did not mention any other localities in his publication (
<bibRefCitation author="Sherriffs, W. R." box="[158,325,292,316]" pageId="132" pageNumber="133" pagination="220 - 253" refId="ref125855" refString="Sherriffs, W. R. (1919) A contribution to the study of South Indian Arachnology. Annuals and Magazine of Natural History, (9 th Series) 4, 220 - 253." type="journal article" year="1919">Sherriffs 1919</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
